Handson4 - Angular Template Driven Forms
Task 1: Build the Enrollment Request Form

Goal: Create a template-driven form using ngModel.

1. Generate Component
ng g c pages/enrollment-form

Add route:
path:'enroll', component:EnrollmentFormComponent

2. enrollment-form.component.html

<form #enrollForm="ngForm" (ngSubmit)="onSubmit(enrollForm)">

<input type="text"
name="studentName"
[(ngModel)]="studentName"
placeholder="Student Name">

<input type="email"
name="studentEmail"
[(ngModel)]="studentEmail"
placeholder="Email">

<input type="number"
name="courseId"
[(ngModel)]="courseId"
placeholder="Course ID">

<select
name="preferredSemester"
[(ngModel)]="preferredSemester">
<option>Odd</option>
<option>Even</option>
</select>

<label>
<input type="checkbox"
name="agreeToTerms"
[(ngModel)]="agreeToTerms">
Agree to Terms
</label>

<button type="submit"
[disabled]="enrollForm.invalid">
Submit
</button>

</form>

3. enrollment-form.component.ts

onSubmit(form:any){
 console.log(form.value);
 console.log(form.valid);
}

Expected:
• Form submits successfully.
• Console displays form values.
• Submit button disabled when form is invalid.

Task 2: Validation and Error Messages

Validation

Student Name:
required
minlength="3"

Email:
required
email

Course ID:
required

Agree To Terms:
required

Error Messages

<span *ngIf="nameCtrl.touched && nameCtrl.errors?.['required']">
Name is required
</span>

<span *ngIf="nameCtrl.touched && nameCtrl.errors?.['minlength']">
Name must be at least 3 characters
</span>

CSS

.ng-invalid.ng-touched{
 border:1px solid red;
}

.ng-valid.ng-touched{
 border:1px solid green;
}

Success Message

<div *ngIf="submitted">
Enrollment request submitted successfully!
</div>

Reset Button

<button
type="button"
(click)="enrollForm.resetForm()">
Reset
</button>

Expected Output

• Validation messages appear.
• Green border for valid fields.
• Red border for invalid fields.
• Success message after submit.
• Reset clears all fields.

